2. **How ViewTube fixes this:** ViewTube gets around this by secretly querying the separate YouTube **Data** API during sync to fetch your 500 most recent uploads so it can pair those Video IDs with their actual titles. 
3. **The bug in this screenshot:** For the videos pictured, they have active analytics data, but they were NOT included in the top 500 list from the Data API (either because they are older than your 500th video or because they are unlisted/private). Since ViewTube had no title to pair it with, it defaulted to calling it "Analytics Row X".

